# Regulatory Disclosures Insurance Contract Pay Out Claim Irrespective Of Protection Wording Indicator

## identifier
de9007

## type
boolean

## definition
Indicate if the insurance contract pays out the claim, irrespective of whether the claim is within the protection wording of the cover offered to the member for all policies.

## guidance
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values
TRUE = insurance contract pays out the claim, irrespective of whether the claim is within the protection wording of the cover offered to the member for all policies
FALSE = insurance contract does not pay out the claim, if the claim is outside the protection wording of the cover offered to the member for all policies

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=RegulatoryDisclosures.InsuranceContractPayOutClaimIrrespectiveOfProtectionWording.Indicator
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.07
- period=duration
